4 unit Belgian Waffle
1.15 ounce Peanut Butter
1 unit Cherry Jam
2 tablespoon Crème Fraîche
2 teaspoon Honey
1 unit Apple
2 teaspoon Sugar
Salt

• Wash and dry produce.

• Halve, core, and thinly slice apple. Toast waffles until golden brown.

• While waffles toast, in a small bowl, whisk together jam, honey, and
1 tsp water (2 tsp for 4 servings) until smooth.

• Place peanut butter and crème fraîche in a second small microwave-safe bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave until peanut butter
is softened, 15-20 seconds. Add 2 tsp sugar (4 tsp for 4 servings), 1 TBSP
water (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of salt; whisk until smooth.

• Divide waffles between plates. Drizzle with as much peanut butter
glaze and jammy honey sauce as you like. Top with apple and serve.